#
# Force LF for all text on every platform. The Windows CI runner's autocrlf would
# otherwise CRLF-convert files on checkout, which breaks two byte-sensitive contracts:
#   1. the SHA-256 integrity check of the vendored cmake/CPM.cmake bootstrap
#      (cmake/Dependencies.cmake; ADR-014 C2) — a CRLF checkout fails the gate at
#      configure time (observed: windows-x64 CI fail ~19s; macOS/Linux LF-only fine).
#   2. the checked-in golden snapshots / preset JSON whose bytes/hashes must match
#      across the bless (macOS) / Linux / Windows boxes.
# No binary assets are tracked today (the only ui/assets are .svg text); revisit if
# any real binary (png/wav/ttf/...) is added — mark it `binary` here.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Belt-and-suspenders for the integrity-checked vendored bootstrap + byte-sensitive corpora.
cmake/CPM.cmake            text eol=lf
tests/golden/corpus/**     text eol=lf
presets/**                 text eol=lf
*.mw101preset              text eol=lf
